H0.text: Elevation is the height above or below sea level.

H1.text: Depth is the term used to describe the height above or below sea level.

H2.text: Latitude is the term used to describe the height above or below sea level.

H3.text: Variation is the height above or below sea level.

A4.text: The elevation of a geographic location is its height above or below a fixed reference point, most commonly a reference geoid, a mathematical model of the Earth's sea level as an equipotential gravitational surface.

A5.text: Depth is used for points below the surface.
